{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|心|亙|t1=heart|t2=partial moon|c1=s|c2=p|ls=ic|ls2=psc}}.

May have originally been written {{zh-l|*亙}}.

In [[w:Seal script|Small Seal Script]], the {{zh-l|*月}} in {{lang|zh|亙}} was written {{zh-l|*舟}}.

===Etymology 1===
Unclear; this word resembles {{och-l|更|id=2}} "change", {{cog|mkh-vie-pro|*k-raːŋʔ||month}}, {{cog|mkh-pea}} ''ka:ŋ'' ~ ''kɔ:ŋ'' ("moon") and is possibly related to {{och-l|姮|tr=*gə̂ŋ}} in {{och-l|姮娥|tr=*gə̂ŋ-ŋâi}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

